time complexity: O(n1 * n2)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We iterate through the characters of s1 and s2 simultaneously. For each character in s1, we check if it matches the character at the same index in s2. If a match is found, we update the maximum repetitions count by adding n1 and n2. This approach has a high efficiency since it only requires two nested loops and has a low energy implication due to its simplicity. The time complexity is O(n1 * n2) because we iterate through both strings once. The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a single integer variable to store the maximum repetitions count.

